    "sub_topic": "Traveling salesman problem",
    "message_1": "A traveling salesman has to visit 5 different cities. The distances between the cities are as follows: \n\n- City 1 to City 2: 5 km\n- City 1 to City 3: 8 km\n- City 1 to City 4: 10 km\n- City 1 to City 5: 6 km\n- City 2 to City 3: 7 km\n- City 2 to City 4: 11 km\n- City 2 to City 5: 8 km\n- City 3 to City 4: 9 km\n- City 3 to City 5: 4 km\n- City 4 to City 5: 3 km\n\nWhat is the shortest possible route for the salesman to visit all cities exactly once and return to the starting city?",
    "message_2": "To find the shortest possible route, we can use the brute force method by listing all possible routes and calculating their total distances. Since there are 5 cities, there are 4! (4 factorial) = 24 possible routes (excluding the starting city and return). Here are the possible routes and their total distances:\n\n1. 1-2-3-4-5-1: 5+7+9+3+6 = 30 km\n2. 1-2-3-5-4-1: 5+7+4+3+10 = 29 km\n3. 1-2-4-3-5-1: 5+11+9+4+6 = 35 km\n4. 1-2-4-5-3-1: 5+11+3+4+8 = 31 km\n5. 1-2-5-3-4-1: 5+8+4+9+10 = 36 km\n6. 1-2-5-4-3-1: 5+8+3+9+8 = 33 km\n7. 1-3-2-4-5-1: 8+7+11+3+6 = 35 km\n8. 1-3-2-5-4-1: 8+7+8+3+10 = 36 km\n9. 1-3-4-2-5-1: 8+9+11+8+6 = 42 km\n10. 1-3-4-5-2-1: 8+9+3+8+5 = 33 km\n11. 1-3-5-2-4-1: 8+4+8+11+10 = 41 km\n12. 1-3-5-4-2-1: 8+4+3+11+5 = 31 km\n13. 1-4-2-3-5-1: 10+11+7+4+6 = 38 km\n14. 1-4-2-5-3-1: 10+11+8+4+8 = 41 km\n15. 1-4-3-2-5-1: 10+9+7+8+6 = 40 km\n16. 1-4-3-5-2-1: 10+9+4+8+5 = 36 km\n17. 1-4-5-2-3-1: 10+3+8+7+8 = 36 km\n18. 1-4-5-3-2-1: 10+3+4+7+5 = 29 km\n19. 1-5-2-3-4-1: 6+8+7+9+10 = 40 km\n20. 1-5-2-4-3-1: 6+8+11+9+8 = 42 km\n21. 1-5-3-2-4-1: 6+4+7+11+10 = 38 km\n22. 1-5-3-4-2-1: 6+4+9+11+5 = 35 km\n23. 1-5-4-2-3-1: 6+3+11+7+8 = 35 km\n24. 1-5-4-3-2-1: 6+3+9+7+5 = 30 km\n\nThe shortest possible route is route 2 and route 18, both with a total distance of 29 km:\n\n1-2-3-5-4-1 and 1-4-5-3-2-1."
